ASD 2025 Apprenticeship Program

ASD Level 2

$57,969 - $60,287 (plus Super)

Brisbane CBD - QLD, Canberra - ACT, Melbourne CBD - VIC, Perth CBD - WA

  

** The Role **

As an apprentice at ASD, your work will support Australia’s national security.
As an apprentice, your work will be supported by ASD mentors and supervisors.
Whether you are a school leaver or looking for a career change, if you have a
passion for Australia’s national security, we encourage you to apply.

You will work three to four days per week with the rest of your time dedicated
to completing a Certificate IV (1.5 years) or a Diploma (2 years). ASD will
pay for your studies as well as your work under a competitive remuneration
package.

In addition to your formal studies, you’ll undertake an extensive internal
training package where you can obtain nationally-recognised qualifications.

  

  

** About our Team **

ASD is entering an exciting phase of growth, innovation and transformation.
Our agency has committed to delivering [ REDSPICE
](https://www.asd.gov.au/sites/default/files/2022-05/ASD-REDSPICE-
Blueprint.pdf) , which is the most significant single investment in the
Australian Signals Directorate’s 75 years.

ASD is seeking applications from school leavers or those looking for a career
change to enter the agency during this unprecedented period of growth

  

  

** Our Ideal Candidate **

** ** Diversity powers our mission. Our work is challenging, and our history shows that the best teams contain a diverse range of people. To achieve our mission, we require people with strong integrity and a mix of skills, passion, adaptability, resilience, curiosity and creativity. 

We support our people to bring their best selves to work. Whether this is
through our diversity and inclusion initiatives, flexible working arrangements
or learning and development opportunities.

We are committed to the growth of our most important resource – you.

You will work as part of a team in an area with the flexibility to work in a
large variety or opportunities in areas including:

  * [ Accounting and Finance ](https://www.asd.gov.au/careers/career-opportunities/accounting-and-finance)
  * [ Administration and Customer Service ](https://www.asd.gov.au/careers/career-opportunities/administration-and-customer-service)
  * [ Auditing, Assurance and Fraud Control ](https://www.asd.gov.au/careers/career-opportunities/audit-assurance-and-fraud-control)
  * [ Cyber Security ](https://www.asd.gov.au/careers/career-opportunities/cyber-security)
  * [ Engineering and Technical ](https://www.asd.gov.au/careers/career-opportunities/engineering-and-technical)
  * [ Human Resources ](https://www.asd.gov.au/careers/career-opportunities/human-resources)
  * [ Information and Communications Technology ](https://www.asd.gov.au/careers/career-opportunities/information-and-communications-technology)
  * [ Information and Knowledge Management ](https://www.asd.gov.au/careers/career-opportunities/information-and-knowledge-management)
  * [ Infrastructure ](https://www.asd.gov.au/careers/career-opportunities/infrastructure)
  * [ Intelligence and analysis ](https://www.asd.gov.au/careers/career-opportunities/intelligence)
  * [ Legal ](https://www.asd.gov.au/careers/career-opportunities/legal)
  * [ Logistics ](https://www.asd.gov.au/careers/career-opportunities/logistics)
  * [ Media and Communications ](https://www.asd.gov.au/careers/career-opportunities/media-and-communication)
  * [ Procurement and Contracting ](https://www.asd.gov.au/careers/career-opportunities/procurement-and-contracting)
  * [ Project and Program management ](https://www.asd.gov.au/careers/career-opportunities/project-and-program-management)
  * [ Security ](https://www.asd.gov.au/careers/career-opportunities/security)
  * [ Strategic and International Policy ](https://www.asd.gov.au/careers/career-opportunities/strategic-and-international-policy)

  

All successful candidates commence their apprenticeship on a salary of $57,969
plus a 4% service allowance and 15.4% superannuation. On successful
completion, apprentices will advance to a higher salary dependent on which
training pathway has been completed.

